Aparently this is the future of dogs… It doesn’t bark, it doesn’t pee in the house. 

So to prove it’s the future I entered my robot dog into a prestigious dog show to try and beat the real thing. Video out now. Woof.

A Dam good birthday 

What a place, anyone wanna sell me a houseboat?

Swapped Amsterdam for some immaculate German town with a castle on the hill, lovely gaff, refreshing river to swim, and some decent schnitzel, think Roos enjoying it too, solid 9/10.

Off to Austria next and then onto lake Como to hopefully rent a boat and force myself to smoke some cigar’s for the gram. VAMOS.

I caught a cloud in a bag and sold it as art

Pretty mental sentence to say but after 3 months of solid graft, waiting on the perfect weather and figuring out how to turning a cloud from the sky into a sellable piece of art, I am now an artist. Refer to me as such.

Ran through the last little bit of Germany and I must say large ratings to our Bavarian brothers and sisters, what a place.

On the road and into Austria, the land of Schnitzel, icy cold mountainous mountain water and pretty unsafe sled rides. Narrowly avoided 3rd degree burns on that one.

Working whilst travelling in a van is way trickier than I thought it would be, when you have so much to explore right outside, sitting on calls and trying to hash through a vid you filmed months prior whilst in a 35 degree tin can isn’t the same as the old Herman miller chair back at home. Better views here though. 

Either way we got the cloud vid out and you lot are loving it so life is good. 

Italy awaits, I can hear the pasta, bruschetta and prosciutto calling my name.
